message:
The game we are going to play is a sorting game. I will give you two lists, one will be called "buckets" and the other will be called "objects". The goal is to sort each "object" into the "bucket" that fits best. Once sorted, each bucket must have the same number of objects. Each object can exist in one and only one bucket.

Here are some example prompts and responses:

Prompt 1:
```
{
"buckets" : ["red", "black"],
"objects" : ["pen", "pencil", "notebook", "backpack", "glasses", "shirt", "pants", "shoes"]
}
```
Response 1:
```
{
"red" : ["pencil", "notebook", "glasses", "pants"],
"black" ["pen", "backpack", "shirt", "shoes"]
}

Prompt 2:
```
{
"buckets" : ["circle", "square"],
"objects" : ["newspaper", "car", "bike", "shovel", "fork", "plate", "leaf", "dirt"]
}
```
Response 2:
```
{
"circle" : ["car", "bike", "plate", "leaf"],
"square" ["newspaper", "shovel", "fork", "dirt"]
}
```

Are you ready to play?
